Nothing needs to be added to .gitignore since the only change is adding a single HTML file (`consorcio-landing/landing-page-completa.html`) which is a source file and should not be ignored.
```
# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build outputs
dist/

# Environment
.env
.env.local
.env.*

# Logs
*.log

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.swp
*.swo

# Coverage
coverage/
htmlcov/
.coverage

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
env/
venv/
.venv/
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt
.tox/
.coverage*
.nosetests*

# Node.js
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
node_modules/
dist/
coverage/
.nyc_output
*.min.js
*.min.css

# Vite specific
.vite/
vite.config.js.timestamp*

# React specific
*.hot-update.js
*.hot-update.json
```
